  "prompt": "How do I get rid of sleepiness in the late morning?",
  "response": "Here are some effective ways to combat late morning sleepiness:\n\n1. Hydration\n- Drink water immediately after waking up\n- Stay hydrated throughout the morning\n\n2. Natural light exposure\n- Open curtains or go outside\n- Sunlight helps regulate your circadian rhythm\n\n3. Physical activity\n- Do light exercises or stretching\n- Take a short walk\n- Do jumping jacks or quick movements\n\n4. Nutrition\n- Eat a balanced breakfast\n- Consume protein and complex carbohydrates\n- Avoid sugary foods that cause energy crashes\n\n5. Caffeine\n- Drink coffee or tea in moderation\n- Avoid excessive caffeine intake\n\n6. Power nap\n- Take a short 10-15 minute nap\n- Avoid longer naps that can make you more groggy\n\n7. Sleep hygiene\n- Maintain a consistent sleep schedule\n- Get 7-9 hours of quality sleep\n- Create a comfortable sleep environment\n\n8. Energy-boosting activities\n- Listen to upbeat music\n- Engage in stimulating conversations\n- Do a mentally engaging task\n\n9. Regulate room temperature\n- Keep your environment slightly cool\n- Avoid overly warm spaces\n\n10. Stress management\n- Practice deep breathing\n- Meditate or do quick relaxation exercises",
